Brightside (www.brightside.com) offers expert, best practice, personalized care for depression and anxiety, from the comfort of home. We use over 100 data points about each patient and our PrecisionRx tool to determine the medication that‚Äôs best, then closely measure and monitor at each step, adjusting medication and dose until it‚Äôs just right. We have a massive and unique data set about depression and anxiety treatments and outcomes. 
We‚Äôre getting phenomenal results: 83% of Brightside members experience a clinically significant symptom reduction and 60% achieve remission levels within 12 weeks. Our mission is to deliver life changing depression and anxiety care to everyone who needs it. 
But there‚Äôs so much more we can do with data to deliver better care and better outcomes to people in need. We can help our members (patients), therapists, and doctors make the most informed decisions at every step in the care cycle, helping each individual get the right treatment and the best results. 
We‚Äôre looking for an outstanding data scientist to help us make it all happen, managing the entire process to deliver impactful clinical decision support that fundamentally changes antidepressant prescribing and clinical outcomes. 
This is a chance to have an important role in an innovative and transformative healthcare company and to positively impact millions of lives. 
Objectives Lead the development of advanced clinical decision support and other solutions, including planning, design, execution, validation, deployment, and maintenance Design and build statistical algorithms and machine learning models to supportive effective clinical decision making on the Brightside platform Carry out first-principles exploratory analysis of our data set Work with engineering to deploy algorithms and models into robust production models Collaborate with designers to determine intuitive and elegant ways of surfacing algorithmic insights to clinicians 
Qualifications MS or Ph.D. degree in Computer Science with a concentration on Artificial Intelligence, Maching Learning, or Statistics. Strong demonstrated expertise in designing, building and deploying statistical algorithms and machine learning models. Expert knowledge of SQL and database operations. Experience with distributed processing methods and ETL systems. Experience with the use of Python to work with large data sets within modern data science frameworks Are capable of working with engineers to build actual production implementations using machine learning and artificial intelligence. Strong communication skills to present insights and summarizing complex data to diverse audiences. 
Preferred qualifications Experience with HIPAA-compliant environments Familiarity with ML/AI workflows (ie. Airflow, Kubeflow, etc) Prior startup experience 
Salary, Benefits, and Perks $160,000 - $200,000 annualized salary based on experience Platinum healthcare, vision and dental Meaningful impact, great people, balanced life, positive and progressive culture. Work remotely and whatever schedule works best for you. We care about results, not 9-5. Unlimited vacation policy Hardware and tools of your choice 
 
